verbose_text: The proteome of MSCs and MSC derived exosomes released under ischemic conditions contained key angiogenic paracrine effectors including platelet derived growth factor (PDGF), epidermal growth factor (EGF), and fibroblast growth factor (FGF); NF-kB signaling was also identified as a key mediator of MSC derived exosome induced angiogenesis in ECs XREF_BIBR.
evidence: MSC-derived exosomes released under ischemic conditions contained key angiogenic paracrine effectors including platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF), epidermal growth factor (EGF), and fibroblast growth factor (FGF); NF-kB signaling was also identified as a key mediator of MSC-derived exosome-induced angiogenesis
